§ ARCHITECTURE (Tauri 2.x · Rust + Webview · ¬ Electron)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ TECH-STACK (bleeding-edge · Apocky-axiom)
  ⊑ Tauri 2.x — Rust-backend + WebView2 (Win) / WKWebView (Mac) / WebKit (Linux) · ~5MB-launcher-+-system-webview
  ⊑ Rust 1.85+ workspace-pinned · matches existing CSSLv3 toolchain
  ⊑ frontend : React 19 + TypeScript 5.x + Vite-build (matches existing cssl-edge stack)
  ⊑ async runtime : Tokio (matches cssl-host-mp-transport-real)
  ⊑ MCP client : reqwest + SSE (server-sent-events) over-localhost:3001
  ⊑ HTTP : ureq for-Anthropic-API-bridge (matches cssl-host-stripe-integration pattern)
  ⊑ storage : SQLite (rusqlite) for-local-session-history · ~10MB cap
  ⊑ key-management : Windows-Credential-Manager (Win) / Keychain (Mac) / libsecret (Linux)
  ⊑ NO Electron · NO Node-runtime-on-host · NO Python · NO JVM

§ BUILD-OUTPUT
  ⊑ Mycelium.exe (Win-x64 · ~30-50 MB · WebView2-runtime-already-present-on-Win10+)
  ⊑ Mycelium.app (Mac-arm64 · ~25 MB future)
  ⊑ Mycelium-linux-x86_64 (AppImage · ~30 MB future)

§ NEW CRATES (workspace · per Unified-Substrate spec/15)
  CRATE-MD-1 NEW `cssl-host-mycelium-desktop` ← Tauri-app crate · main-entry · window-management · MCP-bridge · Anthropic-bridge · local-LLM-bridge
  CRATE-MD-2 NEW `cssl-host-agent-loop` ← agent-loop-state-machine · tool-use · file-edit · git-operations · vercel-deploy · cap-gated
  CRATE-MD-3 NEW `cssl-host-substrate-knowledge` ← embedded-substrate-knowledge · all-specs/grand-vision/*.csl + memory/*.md baked-at-build-time · query-by-relevance via cssl-hdc
  CRATE-MD-4 NEW `cssl-host-llm-bridge` ← unified-LLM-interface · Anthropic-API · Ollama-local · substrate-only fallback · streaming via SSE

§ DEPS-FROM-EXISTING-SUBSTRATE
  ⊑ cssl-host-coder-runtime (W8-F1 ✓ landed) — sandboxed AST-edit-staging · 30-sec-revert · sovereign-cap-required
  ⊑ cssl-host-attestation (W5a ✓ landed) — directive-axis "ImplementationTransparency"
  ⊑ cssl-host-handoff-protocol (W6 ✓ landed) — DM/GM/Collab/Coder routing · cap-bit-bleed defence
