§ THREE-MODE LLM-BRIDGE (self-sufficient discipline)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ MODE-A : EXTERNAL-CLAUDE-API (richest · best-quality · costs-Apocky-tokens)
  ⊑ Apocky pastes-Anthropic-API-key into Settings · stored-OS-keychain · NEVER-disk
  ⊑ HTTPS POST to api.anthropic.com/v1/messages
  ⊑ streaming via SSE · token-usage tracked · cost-counter visible
  ⊑ DEFAULT when-API-key-configured

§ MODE-B : LOCAL-OLLAMA (zero-cost · privacy-max · lower-quality)
  ⊑ detects-running Ollama-instance @ localhost:11434
  ⊑ recommends Apocky `ollama pull qwen2.5-coder:32b` OR `ollama pull deepseek-coder:33b` · best-coder-models for-CSSL/Rust
  ⊑ same OpenAI-compat REST shape · seamless swap from-Mode-A
  ⊑ DEFAULT when-Ollama-running-and-no-Anthropic-key

§ MODE-C : SUBSTRATE-ONLY (¬ LLM · KAN-stage-1 + templated · always-available · stage-0 fallback)
  ⊑ uses cssl-host-kan-real classifiers for-intent-routing
  ⊑ uses cssl-host-gm narrative-templates for-responses
  ⊑ uses cssl-host-coder-runtime for-actual-edit-execution (sovereign-cap-required)
  ⊑ ¬ generative-narrative · stage-0-templated only
  ⊑ FALLBACK · always-available · ¬ external-dep · ¬ local-LLM-required · the-truly-self-sufficient-mode

§ MODE-SWITCHING
  ⊑ Settings-pane : 3 radio-buttons + status-indicators
  ⊑ auto-detect : tries A → B → C in-order · reports-which-active
  ⊑ per-action override : "use stage-0 for-this-message" toggle
  ⊑ session-persistent · saves to ~/.mycelium/config.json

