§ SUBSTRATE-KNOWLEDGE EMBEDDING (knows-the-substrate-as-well-as-Claude)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ BUILD-TIME EMBEDDING (in cssl-host-substrate-knowledge crate)
  ⊑ build.rs reads ALL specs/grand-vision/*.csl (currently 22 files · ~5000 LOC)
  ⊑ build.rs reads ALL ~/.claude/projects/.../memory/*.md (currently ~25 files · ~10000 LOC)
  ⊑ build.rs reads CLAUDE.md + PRIME_DIRECTIVE.md + DECISIONS.md + key README files
  ⊑ build.rs reads DEPRECATED-Infinite-Labyrinth/GDDs/*.md (legacy authoritative-design-source)
  ⊑ ALL-content embedded as `static SUBSTRATE_KNOWLEDGE: phf::Map<&'static str, &'static str>` (perfect-hash-function · O(1) lookup)
  ⊑ accompanying : `static KNOWLEDGE_HDC_INDEX: [(u8; 1250), &'static str]` — pre-computed cssl-hdc 10000-D hypervector for-each-doc · query-time similarity ranks by-cosine

§ QUERY-TIME (in cssl-host-agent-loop crate)
  ⊑ user-query → cssl-hdc-encode → top-K (default 5) similar-docs → inject-into-LLM-context
  ⊑ context-budget : ≤ 50K tokens of-substrate-knowledge per-query · token-aware truncation
  ⊑ "always-loaded" canon : MEMORY.md + CLAUDE.md + PRIME_DIRECTIVE.md (~5K tokens) · no-omit
  ⊑ "loaded-on-relevance" : the rest (specs · memory · GDDs)

§ FRESHNESS
  ⊑ rebuild Mycelium.exe whenever-specs-change-significantly · CI auto-builds nightly
  ⊑ live-update via cssl-host-hotfix-stream (W8-B3 ✓ landed) for-spec-deltas without-full-rebuild

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
§ AGENT-LOOP (the-thing-that-replaces-Claude-loop)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ TURN-STRUCTURE (in cssl-host-agent-loop)
  1 user-input arrives @ chat-window
  2 cssl-host-handoff-protocol classifies : DM | GM | Collab | Coder · cap-check
  3 cssl-host-substrate-knowledge fetches top-K relevant docs
  4 cssl-host-llm-bridge (Mode A/B/C) generates response · with tool-use definitions
  5 if tool-use : execute via tool-handler (file-edit · git · vercel · MCP-call · etc.) · audit-emit
  6 stream response-tokens to-chat-window via Tauri IPC · React-renders
  7 attestation-event written via cssl-host-sigma-chain TIER-1 (LOCAL · always)
  8 cocreative-bias updated based-on Apocky's-feedback (👍 👎 score) · per spec/13 monetization-axiom

§ TOOLS-AVAILABLE (gradual-expansion · all cap-gated)
  T-1 file_read (any-path Apocky-allows · sandbox-list configurable)
  T-2 file_write (sandbox-list-only · cap-gated · auto-revert-30-sec)
  T-3 file_edit (sed-style replacement · diff-shown · approval-required)
  T-4 bash (shell-cmds · Apocky-explicit-approval per-cmd in-stage-0 · per-pattern in-stage-1)
  T-5 git_commit + git_push (auto-staged · message-suggested · approval-required)
  T-6 mcp_call (any of-the-118 LoA-MCP-tools when LoA.exe running · localhost:3001)
  T-7 vercel_deploy (cssl-edge or apocky-com · approval-required)
  T-8 ollama_chat (Mode-B · for-LLM-roundtrip)
  T-9 anthropic_messages (Mode-A · for-LLM-roundtrip)
  T-10 web_search (placeholder · stage-1 · via DuckDuckGo-or-similar HTTP API · per spec/17 cap-NET_HTTP_GET)
  T-11 spec_query (cssl-host-substrate-knowledge query · always-LOCAL · ¬ external)

§ CAP-DISCIPLINE (per spec/10)
  ⊑ Apocky-master-mode = sovereign-cap-on @ all-tools-enabled
  ⊑ default-mode = read-only-tools + bash-with-approval + file-edit-with-approval
  ⊑ paranoid-mode = read-only-tools-only · ¬ writes · ¬ git · ¬ deploy
  ⊑ all-tool-invocations audit-emit · revert-window 30-sec for-mutations
  ⊑ ¬ Coder-can-edit-substrate-* crates · ¬ Coder-can-edit-specs/grand-vision/00..15+ · ¬ Coder-can-modify-TIER-C-secrets

§ AGENT-LOOP-DURATION
  ⊑ single-turn : ≤ 60 sec (warning if-LLM-stalls)
  ⊑ multi-turn-task : N-turns until-Apocky-says-stop · per-turn approval-or-auto
  ⊑ background-mode : cron-schedule like-Claude-Code · self-paced

