§ SECURITY · SOVEREIGNTY · ATTESTATION
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ PER-ACTION-AUDIT
  ⊑ every tool-invocation emits cssl-host-attestation event @ directive-axis "ImplementationTransparency"
  ⊑ every LLM-bridge-call emits attestation @ "Transparency"
  ⊑ every file-mutation emits attestation @ "Sovereignty"
  ⊑ all-events written to-LOCAL Σ-Chain TIER-1 + cssl-host-rt-trace ring · viewable in-Settings → Logs

§ SOVEREIGN-CAP-REVOKE
  ⊑ Ctrl+Shift+Alt+S held-2-seconds @ any-time → revokes-all-active-caps · halts-all-pending-tool-calls · saves-state · returns-to-paranoid-mode
  ⊑ 30-sec-revert-window on-mutations · "undo last-action" button at-all-times
  ⊑ git-staging area for-mutations · Apocky-can-discard before-commit

§ NO-EXFILTRATION
  ⊑ Mycelium NEVER-uploads-Apocky's-code-or-files to-third-party-services without-explicit-approval
  ⊑ LLM-bridge-calls send ONLY user-message + selected-context · NEVER-the-full-codebase
  ⊑ "send selected files for-LLM-context" requires-explicit-tick-of-each-file
  ⊑ per spec/17 TIER-D · player-keys + Σ-mask + Sensitive<*> NEVER-egress

§ STAGE-0-FALLBACK (true-self-sufficiency)
  ⊑ ¬ Anthropic-API + ¬ Ollama → Mode-C-templated-substrate-only
  ⊑ "I cannot reason without an LLM but I can run-tools you-explicitly-invoke" message
  ⊑ tool-use still-works · just-no-natural-language-orchestration
  ⊑ Apocky can-script Mycelium-from-the-substrate-side via-MCP-tools

